{"id":"1872a853-e969-4a0c-b5cf-b02cc685fbe3","timestamp":"2026-03-25T10:12:19.437225037Z","session_id":"eb8f0c90-224a-40a1-a0c2-1816b7b40630","agent_id":null,"agent_role":null,"task_id":null,"action":"PlanCreated","tool_name":null,"params":null,"risk_level":null,"decision":null,"result_success":null,"result_output":"{\"problem_statement\":\"i have container named server-song-stream is restaing en boucle\",\"analysis\":\"## Step 1: Problem Analysis\\n- **What is failing?**: Container named 'server-song-stream' is restarting in a loop (restarting continuously). This indicates the container process exits/crashes, then Docker/container runtime restarts it, and it crashes again.\\n- **Likely components involved**: 1) Application code/configuration inside container, 2) Container runtime (Docker), 3) Resource constraints (memory, CPU), 4) Dependencies (database, external services), 5) Health checks causing restarts.\\n- **Missing information needed**: 1) Container logs showing why it exits, 2) Docker inspect output showing restart policy and exit codes, 3) Resource usage metrics, 4) Application configuration, 5) Health check configuration.\\n\\n## Step 2: Hypothesis Generation\\n**H1 (Most likely)**: Application error/crash - The application inside the container is throwing an unhandled exception or failing to start due to misconfiguration.\\n- Evidence: Container logs showing stack trace or error message before exit.\\n\\n**H2**: Resource exhaustion - Container is hitting memory limit (OOM killer) or CPU constraints.\\n- Evidence: Docker stats showing high memory usage, or OOM killer messages in logs.\\n\\n**H3**: Dependency failure - Application depends on external service (database, API) that is unavailable.\\n- Evidence: Logs showing connection timeouts or dependency errors.\\n\\n**H4**: Health check failure - Docker health check is failing, causing automatic restarts.\\n- Evidence: Docker inspect showing health check configuration and status.\\n\\n**H5**: Port conflict - Application port is already in use on the host.\\n- Evidence: Logs showing 'address already in use' error.\\n\\n## Step 3: Efficient Investigation Strategy\\n1. **First, fastest check**: Get container logs to see why it's exiting (confirms/denies H1, H2, H3, H5).\\n2. **Second check**: Docker inspect to understand restart policy and health checks (confirms/denies H4).\\n3. **Third check**: Check resource usage with docker stats (confirms/denies H2).\\n4. **Fourth check**: Verify dependencies are reachable from container network (confirms/denies H3).\\nAll checks are read-only and can be done in parallel after initial log check.\",\"roles\":[{\"role_name\":\"Container Log Analyst\",\"expertise\":[\"Docker\",\"log analysis\",\"application debugging\"],\"responsibility\":\"Examine container logs and Docker inspect output to identify crash causes\",\"allowed_tools\":[\"shell\",\"log_reader\"],\"token_budget\":50000,\"target_host\":null},{\"role_name\":\"Infrastructure Inspector\",\"expertise\":[\"Docker runtime\",\"resource monitoring\",\"network diagnostics\"],\"responsibility\":\"Check resource usage, network connectivity, and container runtime state\",\"allowed_tools\":[\"shell\"],\"token_budget\":50000,\"target_host\":null}],\"tasks\":[{\"title\":\"Capture container logs and exit codes\",\"description\":\"1. Run 'docker logs server-song-stream --tail 100 --timestamps' to get recent logs\\n2. Run 'docker inspect server-song-stream --format=\\\"{{.State.ExitCode}}\\\"' to get exit code\\n3. Check if logs show application errors, exceptions, or dependency failures\\nDeliverable: Summary of error messages and exit codes from last 5 restarts\",\"assigned_role\":\"Container Log Analyst\",\"depends_on\":[],\"priority\":1,\"hypothesis\":\"H1: Application error/crash\"},{\"title\":\"Analyze Docker configuration and health checks\",\"description\":\"1. Run 'docker inspect server-song-stream' and extract: restart policy, health check config, last health status\\n2. Check if health check is configured and failing\\n3. Verify container configuration matches expected settings\\nDeliverable: Report on restart policy, health check status, and any configuration issues\",\"assigned_role\":\"Container Log Analyst\",\"depends_on\":[],\"priority\":2,\"hypothesis\":\"H4: Health check failure\"},{\"title\":\"Monitor container resource usage\",\"description\":\"1. Run 'docker stats server-song-stream --no-stream' to check current memory/CPU usage\\n2. Check system logs for OOM killer messages: 'dmesg | grep -i oom | tail -10'\\n3. Verify container memory limits: 'docker inspect server-song-stream --format=\\\"{{.HostConfig.Memory}}\\\"' \\nDeliverable: Resource usage metrics and any OOM evidence\",\"assigned_role\":\"Infrastructure Inspector\",\"depends_on\":[],\"priority\":3,\"hypothesis\":\"H2: Resource exhaustion\"},{\"title\":\"Test container network and dependencies\",\"description\":\"1. Get container IP: 'docker inspect server-song-stream --format=\\\"{{.NetworkSettings.IPAddress}}\\\"'\\n2. Test connectivity to common dependencies from within container network namespace\\n3. Check port conflicts: 'netstat -tulpn | grep :<app_port>' (replace with actual port)\\nDeliverable: Network connectivity status and port conflict check\",\"assigned_role\":\"Infrastructure Inspector\",\"depends_on\":[\"Capture container logs and exit codes\"],\"priority\":4,\"hypothesis\":\"H3: Dependency failure or H5: Port conflict\"}],\"synthesis_strategy\":\"1. Combine logs analysis with resource metrics: If logs show OOM messages AND high memory usage → H2 confirmed. 2. Cross-reference exit codes with health check status: If exit code 0 but health check failing → H4 confirmed. 3. Check if error messages match dependency failures → H3 confirmed. 4. Look for 'address already in use' errors → H5 confirmed. 5. If none of above but application errors present → H1 confirmed. Prioritize fixes based on confirmed hypothesis.\"}","tokens_used":null,"hmac":"d0769d3be419625571d36f2cb8701f0135d461ad62a464ecaee24ba350d8172c"}
