{"id":"e0ea105b-7850-4f49-98d4-e539ddf48dfe","timestamp":"2026-03-25T10:14:51.651823099Z","session_id":"1d6be2fa-930d-4074-af56-417d3c833a3c","agent_id":null,"agent_role":null,"task_id":null,"action":"PlanCreated","tool_name":null,"params":null,"risk_level":null,"decision":null,"result_success":null,"result_output":"{\"problem_statement\":\"disk full on /var\",\"analysis\":\"## Step 1: Problem Analysis\\n- **What is failing?** The /var filesystem is at or near 100% capacity, causing potential system instability, application failures, or inability to write logs/process data.\\n- **Components involved:** Filesystem (/var), disk partitions, log files, application data, temporary files, package manager cache, system services writing to /var.\\n- **Missing information:** Which specific files/directories are consuming space, filesystem type, mount options, recent growth patterns, running services affected, whether this is a sudden or gradual issue.\\n\\n## Step 2: Hypothesis Generation\\n1. **H1: Log files have grown excessively** (most likely - /var/log is typically under /var)\\n   - Evidence: Large .log files, rotated logs not cleaned, audit logs, application logs\\n2. **H2: Package manager cache is bloated** (common on Debian/Ubuntu/RHEL systems)\\n   - Evidence: Large /var/cache/apt or /var/cache/yum directories\\n3. **H3: Application data has accumulated** (databases, caches, uploads)\\n   - Evidence: Large /var/lib subdirectories (mysql, postgresql, docker, etc.)\\n4. **H4: Temporary files not cleaned** (stuck in /var/tmp or /var/spool)\\n   - Evidence: Old files in /var/tmp, mail spool, print queues\\n5. **H5: Filesystem corruption or incorrect mount** (least likely but possible)\\n   - Evidence: df vs du mismatch, inode exhaustion, read-only mount\\n\\n## Step 3: Efficient Investigation Strategy\\n- **Fastest check:** Run `df -h` and `du -sh /var/*` to identify largest consumers\\n- **Read-only first:** Analyze disk usage before deleting anything\\n- **Dependencies:** Need to identify WHAT is using space before deciding HOW to fix\\n- **Critical:** Check if system is still operational before attempting cleanup\",\"roles\":[{\"role_name\":\"Filesystem Analyst\",\"expertise\":[\"linux_filesystems\",\"disk_analysis\",\"log_management\"],\"responsibility\":\"Analyze disk usage patterns, identify largest consumers, provide safe cleanup recommendations\",\"allowed_tools\":[\"shell\",\"log_reader\"],\"token_budget\":50000,\"target_host\":null},{\"role_name\":\"System Services Auditor\",\"expertise\":[\"systemd\",\"service_management\",\"process_monitoring\"],\"responsibility\":\"Check which services are affected, identify services writing to /var, verify system stability\",\"allowed_tools\":[\"shell\",\"log_reader\"],\"token_budget\":50000,\"target_host\":null},{\"role_name\":\"Cleanup Specialist\",\"expertise\":[\"safe_deletion\",\"log_rotation\",\"cache_management\"],\"responsibility\":\"Execute safe cleanup operations based on analyst findings, implement preventive measures\",\"allowed_tools\":[\"shell\"],\"token_budget\":50000,\"target_host\":null}],\"tasks\":[{\"title\":\"Assess current disk situation\",\"description\":\"Run `df -h` to confirm /var usage percentage and filesystem type. Run `du -sh /var/* | sort -rh | head -20` to identify top 20 space consumers in /var. Check inode usage with `df -i`. Document findings.\",\"assigned_role\":\"Filesystem Analyst\",\"depends_on\":[],\"priority\":1,\"hypothesis\":\"General assessment needed before testing specific hypotheses\"},{\"title\":\"Check log file consumption\",\"description\":\"Examine /var/log directory: `du -sh /var/log/* | sort -rh`. Check for large log files, verify logrotate configuration with `ls -la /etc/logrotate.d/`. Look for application logs in /var/log that may have grown excessively.\",\"assigned_role\":\"Filesystem Analyst\",\"depends_on\":[\"Assess current disk situation\"],\"priority\":2,\"hypothesis\":\"H1: Log files have grown excessively\"},{\"title\":\"Audit package manager cache\",\"description\":\"Check package cache directories: `/var/cache/apt/` (Debian/Ubuntu), `/var/cache/yum/` (RHEL/CentOS), `/var/cache/pacman/pkg/` (Arch). Run `du -sh` on these directories if they exist. Check last cleanup time.\",\"assigned_role\":\"Filesystem Analyst\",\"depends_on\":[\"Assess current disk situation\"],\"priority\":2,\"hypothesis\":\"H2: Package manager cache is bloated\"},{\"title\":\"Inspect application data directories\",\"description\":\"Check /var/lib subdirectories: `du -sh /var/lib/* | sort -rh | head -10`. Focus on common offenders: mysql, postgresql, docker, containers, libvirt. Check for large database files or container images.\",\"assigned_role\":\"Filesystem Analyst\",\"depends_on\":[\"Assess current disk situation\"],\"priority\":2,\"hypothesis\":\"H3: Application data has accumulated\"},{\"title\":\"Monitor affected services\",\"description\":\"Check which services are failing or experiencing issues due to disk full. Run `systemctl --failed`. Check journal for disk-related errors: `journalctl -p err -b`. Identify services writing to /var.\",\"assigned_role\":\"System Services Auditor\",\"depends_on\":[\"Assess current disk situation\"],\"priority\":3,\"hypothesis\":\"System services may be failing due to disk full\"},{\"title\":\"Execute safe log cleanup\",\"description\":\"Based on findings from task 2: Rotate logs with `logrotate -f /etc/logrotate.conf`, clean old logs with `journalctl --vacuum-size=100M`, remove old log files (keeping recent ones). DO NOT delete active log files.\",\"assigned_role\":\"Cleanup Specialist\",\"depends_on\":[\"Check log file consumption\"],\"priority\":4,\"hypothesis\":\"H1 confirmed - log files need cleanup\"},{\"title\":\"Clean package manager cache\",\"description\":\"If task 3 confirms bloated cache: For apt: `apt-get clean` or `apt-get autoclean`. For yum: `yum clean all`. For dnf: `dnf clean all`. Verify space reclaimed with `df -h`.\",\"assigned_role\":\"Cleanup Specialist\",\"depends_on\":[\"Audit package manager cache\"],\"priority\":4,\"hypothesis\":\"H2 confirmed - package cache needs cleaning\"},{\"title\":\"Implement preventive measures\",\"description\":\"After cleanup: Set up monitoring for /var usage, verify logrotate is working, consider moving large directories to separate partition if recurring issue, document root cause and solution.\",\"assigned_role\":\"Cleanup Specialist\",\"depends_on\":[\"Execute safe log cleanup\",\"Clean package manager cache\"],\"priority\":5,\"hypothesis\":\"Prevent recurrence of disk full condition\"}],\"synthesis_strategy\":\"1. Filesystem Analyst provides disk usage analysis identifying primary space consumers. 2. System Services Auditor confirms which services are affected. 3. Cleanup Specialist executes targeted cleanup based on confirmed hypotheses. 4. All findings combined to determine root cause pattern (logs vs cache vs data) and implement appropriate long-term solution.\"}","tokens_used":null,"hmac":"c7ea24da10b7c5e2e01e14bd83d1c94e95557f846fd912595d46a1c737832b8b"}
